.TH "host1x_syncpt_request" 9 "host1x_syncpt_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
host1x_syncpt_request \- request a syncpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct host1x_syncpt *" host1x_syncpt_request
.BI "(struct host1x_client *client "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
client requesting the syncpoint
.IP "flags" 12
flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
host1x client drivers can use this function to allocate a syncpoint for
subsequent use. A syncpoint returned by this function will be reserved for
use by the client exclusively. When no longer using a syncpoint, a host1x
client driver needs to release it using \fBhost1x_syncpt_free\fP.
